f" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1450<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/03 12:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=903.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing until bonds of force..</span><hr size=1> At the lowest levels you need to use a weapon.  I recommend 1HB or piercing.  At levels 1-3 go to any newbie zone and use shock of frost to pull and hit/stab them until they die.  <br>
<br>
At level 4 you get the root spell.  You can solo by rooting stuff and blasting it while it is rooted.  This technique is called root-and-nuke.  For soloing this is your bread and butter at low levels.  Roots will break fairly often when you nuke, so the technique isn't perfect.  The spell is somewhat unreliable at first but gets better.  You will still want to have a weapon equipped because your hits will still be effective well into your teens.  <br>
<br>
The other wizard soloing technique I know of is to speed-kite.  You get a SoW and just cast you biggest dd on a mob to pull it, then run ahead, nuke, run ahead, nuke, etc. until dead.  This technique is more risky but can reap better rewards.  For instance, wizards get spells that are able to hit four mobs simultaneously (column and pillar series).  These are used for multi- or quad-kiting.  Our snare spell is AOE and affects up to four targets, just like the column/pillar line so once a wizard gets snare he/she is a quad-kiting fool.  Again, since you don't have snare you will need to speed-kite until level 29 when you get the snare spell.  Unless you can find an item with snare charges on it.<br>
<br>
Plus its a good idea to do groups at these levels as well as soloing so you learn group mechanics as a wizard.  <br>
<br>
A good path is newbie zones until lvl 11, Kurn's Tower (11-16), Paludal Caverns (17-24) and High Keep (25-32).  Alternatively (and arguably better xp) you can go to Marus Seru (23-30) and then Dawnshroud Peaks (30-?) to group or solo.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nathos>Nathos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/03 6:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=903.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing until bonds of force..</span><hr size=1> pauladal caves is soloable FAR before 17 I take all my low level toons up there at level 6 now if you go in from the ? var shal?  (kitty citty) side there are  small shrooms and such that are great exp and easily soloable there<br>
