I would Try and get Jboots at all costs they will end up saving you a ton of cash and your life more than anything else... <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.PageProducer.com/users/Sibian/Lighthammersig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=llyapakadeabn>Llyap aka Deabn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/03 7:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=903.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing until bonds of force..</span><hr size=1> It is quite possible to solo without snare. At first you will solo by going toe to toe with a mob and nuking between hitrounds. You will likely slowly fade out of melee range fighting. At this point just keep the mobs away from you by a mix of only casting on the mobs when they are at max distance from you and rooting. For example root a mob, if root resists run as fast as you can then stop and cast root again. Then move to max casting range and nuke it. Also if you can outrun the mob you can just run, nuke, run, nuke.<br>
<br>
Also you can quad kite starting at 8, although I am not sure if you will be able to get efficient xp and unless you find something that runs slow you will need to get an SoW. Just use Column of Frost and the level one nuke. Use your level one nuke (or any other method) to aggro 4 mobs. Run circles so the mobs are close. Then you just run away and then cast the column, repeat the running and casting until the mobs die. It is fun to experiment with, I suggest you try it when you are board and have an SoW. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bayler>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 5:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=903.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing until bonds of force..</span><hr size=1> Assuming you're untwinked and can't afford JBoots or a ton of SoW potions - which is likely if you're starting on a brand new server - you can fall back on conventional tactics.<br>
<br>
Root &amp; Nuke - Not a lot to it.  Just make sure you stand far enough back that you can re-root when it breaks.<br>
<br>
Nuke-stun-nuke - At certain levels, you can fire off this combo and kill a mob without a whole lot of space.  It works best if the mob is weak enough for you to survive a couple hits though.<br>
<br>
Bolt-bolt-nuke - Bolts are great, for the levels we get them.  They're longer-ranged than our nukes, and they actually take time to travel.  If you get the timing down, you can fire off a couple and finish with a shock before the mob gets to you.  Bolts are somewhat flaky though; you need to worry about line of sight and distance and other such hazzards.  But at certain levels and in certain places, it's more efficient than trying to root all the time.  Keep root memmed, though.<br>
<br>
Shadowstep-gate - For when you need to get away.  In particular, if you get adds.  After all, you can't count on root to hold while you run, unsowed, across WK.  Shadowstep (or Fade, or Yonder) work best when you're on high terrain.  It won't help you much in a dungeon; but in a place like Erud's Crossing - an island in the ocean - you'll almost always get away. <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
Tessally - 54 Nun of Solusek Ro - Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athousandyoung>AThousandYoung</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 4:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=903.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing until bonds of force..</span><hr size=1> You can quad beetles in North Karana in your late teens without SOW.  They run slow. <p>Caffron, Wizard of &lt;<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/bsanctuslumen" target="top">Sanctus Lumen</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->&gt;, the Good team PK guild.</p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19>Soloing and Quad-Kiting</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.242<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

